The memo: -

Under the Vasantrao Naik Tanda Habitat Improvement Scheme, as per the Government Decisions in Reference No. 1 to 11, Jalna district has been provided Rs. A total of 452 works with an outlay of ₹1 lakh have been given administrative sanction and a total of ₹1 lakh has been sanctioned for these works. 467.00 Lakhs of funds have been disbursed. As per the Government Decisions in Reference No.12 to 16, the availability of such works from time to time is Rs. An amount of 925.00 lakh has been made available. Thus, for 452 such works, a total of Rs. 1392.00 Lakhs of funds have been disbursed and the remaining funds will be released as per the completion of works and availability of funds.

2. A proposal to fund 114 completed works out of the total 452 works mentioned above has been received by the Government under letter No. 17. In pursuance of this proposal, the following 114 completed works have been sanctioned at present at a cost of Rs. The memorandum provides for the approval of the Government to disburse funds to the tune of 64,32,000 - (Rupees Sixty-four lakh and Thirty-five thousand only). Also, the remaining funds will be disbursed as per the availability of funds under the said scheme.
(Rs. in Lakhs)
